    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p rend="align(center)">
                <placeName>N 40 South St</placeName>
            </p>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>N York</placeName>
                <date>May 26th 1864</date>
            </p>
            <p>My dear <addressee>Mr Leeser</addressee></p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I duly recd your favor of <date>9th</date><lb/> inst. and ever since
                have been waiting<lb/> an opportunity to reply thereto. But it<lb/> has seemed
                between church Bank<lb/> &amp; nursery matters and 5 or 6 Hours<lb/> consumed daily
                in traveling—that<lb/> I have not a moments time for<lb/> anything else.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Perhaps you have not heard that<lb/>
                <persName>Mrs Hanford</persName> some 10 days since presented<lb/> me with twin
                Babies—a Girl &amp; a Boy—<lb/> please tell <persName>Mrs Cozens</persName>. The
                mother &amp;<lb/> children are doing remarkably well.<lb/> Besides this a new Bank
                has just been<lb/> organized at <placeName>So Norwalk</placeName> of which I am<lb/>
                Director &amp; Vice President which takes up<lb/> all my evenings—being chairman of
                the<lb/> committee on By Laws &amp; a member of</p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p><sic>of</sic> any other committee on Building<lb/> Safes &amp;c.</p>
            <p>Your Parcels have been regularly<lb/> recd and contents distributed as
                addressed.<lb/> The Am European Express Co. people<lb/> say your parcels have all
                been ditd<lb/> and recd in <placeName>England</placeName>. They also say<lb/> they
                will have to raise the price<lb/> of Freight, but could not then say<lb/> how
                much.</p>
            <p>I enclose the Express Co. receipts<lb/> for the last 3 Parcels.</p>
            <p>Are you not afraid your paper<lb/> will be stopped a guard of <add>?</add><lb/> Bucks
                put over your types &amp; yourself<lb/> consigned to <placeName>Fort
                    Lafayette</placeName>. (I wonder<lb/> what that illustrious Patriot would
                say<lb/> if he could know how his name is<lb/> being desecrated). The <hi
                    rend="underline">Autocrat</hi><lb/> might with equal justice do these<lb/>
                things to us or any one else as to have done<lb/> it to Parties here for publishing
                with</p>
            <pb n="3"/>
            <p>the best instructions—a matter of such<lb/> vital importance and with such
                semblance<lb/> of truth &amp; genuineness. A Forgery perpe<lb/>trated &amp;
                concocted by one of the<lb/> many fanatics and adherents of the<lb/>
                administration.</p>
            <p>With much love to <persName>Mrs Cozens</persName><lb/> &amp;
                    <persName>Ella</persName>. I remain in great haste</p>
            <p rend="indent(6)">Your sincere Friend</p>
            <p rend="indent(7)">
                <persName role="author">H S. Hanford</persName>
            </p>
        </body>
